Pitney Bowes Inc. said it completed its previously announced acquisition of the contract-services business of Pandick Inc., significantly expanding its own business of managing others' mailrooms. 

Terms weren't disclosed.
Pitney Bowes, a marketing and manufacturing company, will operate the business, Pandick Technologies Inc., within its own management-services organization. 

New York-based Pandick went private in a leveraged buy-out in 1986.
It reported revenue of nearly $100 million for the year ended Aug. 31. 

